{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Day 3: Building a RAG Pipeline – Core Components\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objective:** Build the core RAG ingestion pipeline – loading, chunking, embedding, and vector storage.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Topics:**\n",
    "- Loading PDF/text files using LangChain document loaders\n",
    "- Splitting documents into overlapping chunks with `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter`\n",
    "- Generating embeddings (HuggingFace or OpenAI)\n",
    "- Storing embeddings in Pinecone via LangChain\n",
    "- Running similarity search queries\n",
    "\n",
    "> 💡 **Memory aid**: RAG = Retrieval Augmented Generation. Today we focus on **retrieval** (ingestion) – tomorrow we optimise and evaluate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup & Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Core libraries\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "import pinecone\n",
    "from langchain.document_loaders import TextLoader, PyPDFLoader\n",
    "from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\n",
    "from langchain.embeddings import OpenAIEmbeddings\n",
    "from langchain.vectorstores import Pinecone as LangChainPinecone\n",
    "from langchain.schema import Document\n",
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load environment variables (create .env file with your API keys)\n",
    "load_dotenv()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Libraries loaded. Checking environment...\")\n",
    "pinecone_api_key = os.getenv(\"PINECONE_API_KEY\")\n",
    "openai_api_key = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not pinecone_api_key:\n",
    "    print(\"⚠️ PINECONE_API_KEY not found in .env file\")\n",
    "if not openai_api_key:\n",
    "    print(\"⚠️ OPENAI_API_KEY not found in .env file\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"✅ Environment looks good.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Create Sample Documents (if you have no PDFs)\n",
    "\n",
    "For practice, we'll create a few sample text files about finance regulations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a sample directory and text files\n",
    "sample_dir = \"../data/sample_financial_docs\"\n",
    "os.makedirs(sample_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "docs = {\n",
    "    \"basel_iii.txt\": \"\"\"Basel III is a global regulatory framework for banks. It requires minimum capital ratios: Common Equity Tier 1 (CET1) of 4.5%, Tier 1 capital of 6%, and total capital of 8%. Additionally, a capital conservation buffer of 2.5% is required, bringing total capital requirement to 10.5%.\"\"\",\n",
    "    \"gdpr.txt\": \"\"\"The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is a European Union regulation on data protection and privacy. Key articles: Article 5 (principles), Article 17 (right to erasure), Article 32 (security). Any company processing EU citizens' data must comply, regardless of location.\"\"\",\n",
    "    \"soc2.txt\": \"\"\"SOC 2 is a auditing standard for service organizations. It defines trust service criteria: security, availability, processing integrity, confidentiality, and privacy. SOC 2 reports are essential for cloud vendors handling sensitive data.\"\"\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "for filename, content in docs.items():\n",
    "    with open(os.path.join(sample_dir, filename), 'w') as f:\n",
    "        f.write(content)\n",
    "print(f\"Created {len(docs)} sample documents in {sample_dir}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Loading Documents with LangChain Document Loaders\n",
    "\n",
    "LangChain provides loaders for various formats. We'll use `TextLoader` for .txt files."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load all text files from the directory\n",
    "from langchain.document_loaders import DirectoryLoader\n",
    "\n",
    "loader = DirectoryLoader(sample_dir, glob=\"**/*.txt\", loader_cls=TextLoader)\n",
    "documents = loader.load()\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(documents)} documents.\")\n",
    "for doc in documents:\n",
    "    print(f\"- {doc.metadata['source']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Examine one document\n",
    "print(documents[0].page_content[:200])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Chunking – Splitting into Overlapping Segments\n",
    "\n",
    "We use `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` – it tries to split on natural boundaries (paragraphs, sentences)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "text_splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(\n",
    "    chunk_size=200,        # maximum characters per chunk\n",
    "    chunk_overlap=20,      # overlap between chunks (for context continuity)\n",
    "    length_function=len,\n",
    "    separators=[\"\\n\\n\", \"\\n\", \" \", \"\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "chunks = text_splitter.split_documents(documents)\n",
    "print(f\"Original documents: {len(documents)} → Chunks: {len(chunks)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show first chunk\n",
    "print(\"\\n--- First Chunk ---\")\n",
    "print(chunks[0].page_content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Generating Embeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "Embeddings convert text into vectors (lists of floats). We'll use OpenAI's embeddings (requires API key).\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Alternative:** If you don't have OpenAI, uncomment the HuggingFace option (free, but slower)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize embeddings model\n",
    "embeddings = OpenAIEmbeddings(model=\"text-embedding-ada-002\")  # or \"text-embedding-3-small\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Alternative: HuggingFaceEmbeddings (no API key required)\n",
    "# from langchain.embeddings import HuggingFaceEmbeddings\n",
    "# embeddings = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(model_name=\"sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test embedding on a sentence\n",
    "test_text = \"Basel III capital requirements\"\n",
    "test_vector = embeddings.embed_query(test_text)\n",
    "print(f\"Embedding dimension: {len(test_vector)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"First 5 values: {test_vector[:5]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Setting Up Pinecone Vector Database\n",
    "\n",
    "Pinecone is a managed vector database. We'll create an index if it doesn't exist."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize Pinecone\n",
    "pc = pinecone.Pinecone(api_key=pinecone_api_key)\n",
    "\n",
    "index_name = \"rag-workshop\"\n",
    "dimension = len(test_vector)  # 1536 for ada-002, 384 for MiniLM\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check if index exists, create if not\n",
    "if index_name not in pc.list_indexes().names():\n",
    "    pc.create_index(\n",
    "        name=index_name,\n",
    "        dimension=dimension,\n",
    "        metric=\"cosine\",\n",
    "        spec=pinecone.ServerlessSpec(cloud=\"aws\", region=\"us-east-1\")\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\"Created index '{index_name}'\")\n",
    "    # Wait for index to be ready\n",
    "    while not pc.describe_index(index_name).status['ready']:\n",
    "        time.sleep(1)\n",
    "    print(\"Index ready.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"Index '{index_name}' already exists.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Storing Chunks and Embeddings in Pinecone\n",
    "\n",
    "LangChain's `Pinecone` wrapper simplifies this."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create vector store and add documents\n",
    "vector_store = LangChainPinecone.from_documents(\n",
    "    chunks,\n",
    "    embeddings,\n",
    "    index_name=index_name\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"Added {len(chunks)} chunks to Pinecone index '{index_name}'\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Running Similarity Search\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we can query the vector store."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "query = \"What is the capital requirement under Basel III?\"\n",
    "results = vector_store.similarity_search(query, k=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Query: {query}\\n\")\n",
    "for i, doc in enumerate(results):\n",
    "    print(f\"Result {i+1}:\")\n",
    "    print(doc.page_content)\n",
    "    print(f\"Source: {doc.metadata.get('source', 'unknown')}\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Try another query\n",
    "query2 = \"What does GDPR say about data deletion?\"\n",
    "results2 = vector_store.similarity_search(query2, k=1)\n",
    "print(\"Top result:\")\n",
    "print(results2[0].page_content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Optional: Similarity Search with Score\n",
    "\n",
    "Sometimes you want the similarity score as well."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Using the underlying Pinecone index directly\n",
    "# This returns scores (cosine similarity, higher = more similar)\n",
    "query_embedding = embeddings.embed_query(\"SOC 2 trust principles\")\n",
    "index = pc.Index(index_name)\n",
    "response = index.query(\n",
    "    vector=query_embedding,\n",
    "    top_k=2,\n",
    "    include_metadata=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "for match in response.matches:\n",
    "    print(f\"Score: {match.score:.3f} - {match.metadata.get('text', '')[:100]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Clean Up (Optional)\n",
    "\n",
    "Delete the Pinecone index when you're done to avoid charges (optional)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Uncomment to delete the index (cannot be undone)\n",
    "# pc.delete_index(index_name)\n",
    "# print(f\"Deleted index '{index_name}'\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
